
Design Specifications
Project:	Autonomous Remote Controlled Boat
Date:	 	3/30/2026
Version: 1.0
Authors: 	Connor Snell, Wyatt Snell

Objectives:
•	The goal will be to get the boat to go in a straight line using gps of the area.
•	The boat will have obstacle avoidance.
•	Have a safeguard by Bluetooth to deactivate and reactivate as needed.
•	Make a personal app that allows user interface to change coordinates for boats destination.

Successes:
A success is counted if it achieves these specifications
•	The boat can carry up to 5 lbs.
•	The boat successfully reaches the designated area.
•	The boat successfully activates and deactivates on demand.
•	App interacts with the boat on user demand.
Constraints:
•	Budget is set at $500
•	Maximum weight set at 5lbs 
•	Power is with battery and servo motors.
•	Battery must last 30 minutes.

